        {
            "id": 19,
            "cardSet": 7,
            "title": "City Manager's Message",
            "body": [
                "<p>May 26, 2015</p>\n<p>Honorable Mayor Manheimer and City Council Members:</p>\n<p>It is my pleasure to respectfully submit to you the City Manager's Proposed Budget for the fiscal year\nbeginning July 1, 2015 and ending June 30, 2016 with a total operating budget of $154 million. The proposed\nbudget includes a total General Fund Budgetof $103 million, a 3.6% increase over the adopted fiscal year\n2014-2015 budget. The proposed budget includes an increase to the property tax rate of 1.5 cents per $1000\nof valuation, bringing the total millage rate to 47.5 cents.</p>"
            ],
            "image": null,
            "link": "/docs/asheville/2-ManagersLetter_FY2016.pdf",
            "dataType": "card"
        },
        {
            "id": 20,
            "cardSet": 7,
            "title": "Organizational Structure",
            "body": [
                "<p>Understand the organizational structure underlying the City's operating budget. Click <a href=\"http://www.ashevillenc.gov/Portals/0/city-documents/communityrelations/about_city_government/COA%20Organizational%20Chart%20041615.pdf\">here</a> for a full-size version\nof the organization chart at left.</p>"
            ],
            "image": "/img/cards/pic561588c3deef6.jpg",
            "link": "/docs/asheville/3-Introduction.pdf",
            "dataType": "card"
        },
        {
            "id": 21,
            "cardSet": 7,
            "title": "Budget Process",
            "body": [
                "<p>Budget preparation affords departments the opportunity to reassess their goals and objectives\nand the strategies for accomplishing them. Even though the proposed budget may be heard by\nCity Council in May and adopted in June, its preparation begins at least six months prior\nwith projections of City reserves, revenues, and financial capacity.</p>",
                "<p>Read more about:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Financial forecasting</li>\n<li>City Council Strategic Planning</li>\n<li>Departmental Budget Development</li>\n<li>City Manager Review</li>\n<li>Budget Adoption</li>\n<li>Budget Amendments and Revisions</li>\n<li>Basis of Budgeting</li>\n</ul>"
            ],
            "image": null,
            "link": "/docs/asheville/Budget_Process.pdf",
            "dataType": "card"
        },
        {
            "id": 22,
            "cardSet": 7,
            "title": "FY 2015-16 Budget Calendar",
            "body": [
                "<p>Examine the detailed calendar of steps over the past year that led to the proposed budget.</p>"
